description: Lists the FinSpace Changesets for a Dataset.

parameters.name: datasetId
parameters.description: The unique identifier for the FinSpace Dataset to which the Changeset belongs.

return_structure.name: changesets
return_structure.description: (dict) --- Response to ListChangesetsResponse. This returns a list of dataset changesets that match the query criteria.

nested_items.name: changesets
nested_items.description: List of Changesets found.

nested_items.name: changesetId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier for a Changeset.

nested_items.name: changesetArn
nested_items.description: The ARN identifier of the Changeset.

nested_items.name: datasetId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier for the FinSpace Dataset in which the Changeset is created.

nested_items.name: changeType
nested_items.description: Type that indicates how a Changeset is applied to a Dataset.
REPLACE --- Changeset is considered as a replacement to all prior loaded Changesets.
APPEND --- Changeset is considered as an addition to the end of all prior loaded Changesets.
MODIFY --- Changeset is considered as a replacement to a specific prior ingested Changeset.

nested_items.name: sourceParams
nested_items.description: Options that define the location of the data being ingested.
(string) ---
(string) ---

nested_items.name: formatParams
nested_items.description: Options that define the structure of the source file(s).
(string) ---
(string) ---

nested_items.name: createTime
nested_items.description: The timestamp at which the Changeset was created in FinSpace. The value is determined as epoch time in milliseconds. For example, the value for Monday, November 1, 2021 12:00:00 PM UTC is specified as 1635768000000.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: Status of the Changeset ingestion.
PENDING --- Changeset is pending creation.
FAILED --- Changeset creation has failed.
SUCCESS --- Changeset creation has succeeded.
RUNNING --- Changeset creation is running.
STOP_REQUESTED --- User requested Changeset creation to stop.

nested_items.name: errorInfo
nested_items.description: The structure with error messages.

nested_items.name: errorMessage
nested_items.description: The text of the error message.

nested_items.name: errorCategory
nested_items.description: The category of the error.
VALIDATION --- The inputs to this request are invalid.
SERVICE_QUOTA_EXCEEDED --- Service quotas have been exceeded. Please contact AWS support to increase quotas.
ACCESS_DENIED --- Missing required permission to perform this request.
RESOURCE_NOT_FOUND --- One or more inputs to this request were not found.
THROTTLING --- The system temporarily lacks sufficient resources to process the request.
INTERNAL_SERVICE_EXCEPTION --- An internal service error has occurred.
CANCELLED --- Cancelled.
USER_RECOVERABLE --- A user recoverable error has occurred.

nested_items.name: activeUntilTimestamp
nested_items.description: Time until which the Changeset is active. The value is determined as epoch time in milliseconds. For example, the value for Monday, November 1, 2021 12:00:00 PM UTC is specified as 1635768000000.

nested_items.name: activeFromTimestamp
nested_items.description: Beginning time from which the Changeset is active. The value is determined as epoch time in milliseconds. For example, the value for Monday, November 1, 2021 12:00:00 PM UTC is specified as 1635768000000.

nested_items.name: updatesChangesetId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the Changeset that is updated.

nested_items.name: updatedByChangesetId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the updated Changeset.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: A token that indicates where a results page should begin.
